title: Brown Buttabean's weigh-in stunt fires up Southland's Kaleni Taetuli
text:
Brown Buttabean's weigh-in stunt fires up Southland's Kaleni Taetuli LOGAN SAVORY Last updated 15:52, October 14 2015 RORY O'SULLIVAN/Stuff.co.nz 
Dave Letele - dubbed 'The Brown Buttabean' - lashes out at Kaleni Taetuli at the weight-in for their bout at Auckland's Trusts Arena on Thursday night. 
Dave 'The Brown ' Letele continues to live his life as a publicity stunt, but his latest actions may not have helped his chances in a redemption bout against Southland's Kaleni Taetuli in Auckland on Thursday night. 
The loud-mouthed promoters tool lashed out at Taetuli as the two traded words at the weigh-in in Auckland on Wednesday. 
Letele himself acknowledges he is paid to promote first with the boxing component secondary. His stunt at the pre-fight weigh-in yet again highlights that. Nicole Johnstone 
Dave 'The Brown Buttabean' Letele, left, and Kaleni Taetuli at their weigh in ahead of their fight on Thursday night. 
However, it seems the shove and the war of words have again provided the spark Taetuli was after, leading into the fight. 
The pair fought in Invercargill in August and when Letele entered the ring he shoved Taetuli moments before the fight started.
